hopobject.body: Thanks for calling shatavari for male There is some resistance among Republicans in the Senate on the House GOP plan. "I'm not in the shut-down-the-government crowd, I'm in the take-over-the-government crowd," said Sen. Lamar Alexander, R-Tenn. Alexander said the policy goal of dismantling the law among Republicans is the same, but the tactics are different. He said he believes Republicans should focus on making the case to the electorate ahead of the 2014 and 2016 elections. "Only when we elect more (Republicans) senators can we actually change Obamacare," he said.
